Gwen Lee https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gwen_Lee 0 Gwen Lee (born Gwendolyn Lepinski, November 12, 1904 – August 20, 1961) was an American stage and film actress. Lee began her career as a model before being discovered and signed to Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer. She was typically cast in supporting roles. Lee appeared in over sixty films before retiring in 1938.
